articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Ukrainian president Volodymyr Zelenskiy awarded two Polish volunteers state awards during a stopover on Saturday, but did not meet any officials as relations between the two countries are strained over grain imports.
articles.title: Ukraine's Zelenskiy stops over in Poland to award two volunteers

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: U.S. Ambassador to Canada David Cohen confirmed that "shared intelligence among Five Eyes partners" had informed Canadian Prime Minister Justin Trudeau of the possible involvement of Indian agents in the murder of a Canadian citizen in June, CTV News reported.
articles.title: Shared intelligence from Five Eyes informed Trudeau's India allegation, CTV News reports

articles.author: Francis Kokoroko
articles.description: Hundreds of demonstrators gathered in the Ghanaian capital Accra on Saturday for a third day of anti-government protests linked to economic hardship that have led to dozens of arrests.
articles.title: Multi-day protests over economic crisis grip Ghana's capital

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Lebanon's army said it fired tear gas at Israeli forces over the border on Saturday in response to smoke bombs fired at its troops, though Israel said Lebanon started the confrontation.
articles.title: Lebanese army says it exchanged tear gas, smoke bomb fire with Israel

articles.author: Philip Pullella
articles.description: Pope Francis on Saturday condemned "belligerent nationalisms" and called for a pan-European response to migration to stop the Mediterranean, where thousands have drowned, from becoming "the graveyard of dignity".
articles.title: No 'sea of death': Pope calls for pan-European action on migration

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Uganda's President Yoweri Museveni said on Saturday an air strike by the east African country's military had killed members of an Islamic State (IS)-allied rebel group including a key person responsible for bomb attacks in Uganda's capital.
articles.title: Uganda leader says air strike killed fighters of IS-allied rebel group in Congo

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: A large chunk of a motorway in southwest Sweden collapsed overnight, causing three people to be taken to hospital with light injuries, police said on Saturday.
articles.title: Landslide causes large chunk of Swedish motorway to collapse

articles.author: Doyinsola Oladipo, Abhirup Roy
articles.description: U.S. auto workers expanded their strike on Friday with a clear target for distress: dealers who sell and service GM and Stellantis vehicles.
articles.title: GM, Stellantis dealers and customers face dwindling parts as UAW strike expands

articles.author: Michelle Nichols, Gabriela Baczynska
articles.description: Russia's Foreign Minister Sergei Lavrov on Saturday dismissed the West as an "empire of lies" and said the latest U.N. proposals to revive the Black Sea grain initiative would not fly because they do not deliver on promises made to Moscow.
articles.title: Russia's Lavrov calls West 'empire of lies,' dismisses grain-deal revival bid

articles.author: Trevor Hunnicutt, Nandita Bose
articles.description: The Biden administration is in talks with Vietnam over an agreement for the largest arms transfer in history between the ex-Cold War adversaries, according to two people familiar with a deal that could irk China and sideline Russia.
articles.title: Exclusive: Biden aides in talks with Vietnam for arms deal that could irk China
